Argued and submitted April 24, 1991, affirmed February 12, 1992 ALFREDO CESSPOOCH, Appellant, v. Manfred (Fred) MAASS, Respondent. (90-C-11170; CA A66857) 825 P2d 655 Timothy A. Sylwester, Assistant Attorney General, Salem, argued the cause for respondent. With him on the brief were Dave Frohnmayer, Attorney General, and Virginia L. Linder, Solicitor General, Salem. PER CURIAM

Joseph, C. J., vice Newman, J., deceased.

Hari Nam S. Khalsa, Salem, argued the cause for appellant. With him on the brief was Public Defender’s Office, Salem.

Before Richardson, Presiding Judge, and Joseph, Chief Judge, and Deits, Judge.
